- The angular acceleration $\alpha$ is related to torque by $\tau=I \alpha$, where $I=\frac{1}{2} M R^2$ for a solid disk. <marks>1 mark</marks>

$$
\begin{gathered}
I=\frac{1}{2} \times 2.0 \times(0.40)^2=0.16 \, \mathrm{kg\,m^2} \\
\alpha=\frac{\tau}{I}=\frac{4.0}{0.16}=25 \, \mathrm{rad\,s^{-2}}
\end{gathered}
$$

<marks>1 mark</marks>
